<TEXT>
the city where tough guys frank sinatra and 
g gordon liddy grew up has voted to replace the gritty docks 
featured in the movie on the waterfront with condominiums and 
offices 
by a nearly 21 margin tuesday voters in the one squaremile 
city rejected a referendum that would have converted the 31acre 
hudson river waterfront tract into a park with a tremendous view of 
the manhattan skyline 
the vote shows the concern of the city about being rational in 
the proportion of parklands said councilman steve cappiello one 
of the leaders against the referendum i think the area is 
located so that it would not have too much impact on the city of 
hoboken 
cappello said wednesday that city leaders want to convert the 
prime waterfront space into office and residential space 
the issue highlights the friction caused by the rapid 
gentrification the hudson county community is undergoing newer and 
younger residents many of whom fled manhattan for lower rents 
sought the park older residents want the tax revenues that new 
development might bring to the city 
