<TEXT>
the scales of justice took on a 
whole new meaning when a man decided to try and prevent a detroit 
suburb from making him move 16 boa constrictors and pythons out of 
his onebedroom apartment 
eric larson 26 who owns the snakes has sued sterling heights 
to prevent its enforcement of an ordinance that makes it illegal to 
keep an animal not commonly kept or housed as a household pet 
said lori finazzo an assistant city attorney 
two of larsons pets colah a 10foot 50pound anaconda and 
beauregard a 2foot bolivian redtailed boa constrictor were 
entered monday as evidence by defense attorney charles langton 
larson lifted colah from its cage and wrapped the snake around 
his neck while explaining to macomb county circuit judge raymond 
cashen that he lets eight of his larger snakes slither freely 
around his apartment the eight smaller snakes are kept in cages in 
the bedroom while larson sleeps in the living room he said 
the prosecution is arguring that the snakes could escape through 
plumbing and make their way to other apartments 
anacondas are aquatic finazzo said theyll go straight 
for the toilet 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
some sports fans are getting a chance to 
show their stuff on the evening sportscast but if theyre not a 
hit with viewers they may be hit with a gong 
ten people including billy martin jr son of the former 
yankees manager are getting their shot on kamctv 
the abc affiliate has uirged viewers to call in and rate the 
performances 
those who flunk get to watch kamctv news director larry elliott 
pull out his mallet and strike the gong ending their brief 
broadcasting careers 
after the stations sports director left last month elliott 
announced on the air that he was accepting applications from any 
resident with guts enough to appear on the 6 pm newscast and read 
the sports news 
you always figure theres someone out there that could do it 
but doesnt think they could or hasnt had the opportunity said 
elliott a former welder who believes ordinary people can present 
news as well as professionals 
the contest ends friday 
elliott concedes he may end up hiring a professional but before 
he does he plans to broadcast some of the audition videotapes hes 
gotten 
the professionals will face a callin vote and the gong just 
like the amateurs elliott said 
