<TEXT>
millionaire businessman pj morgan was 
elected mayor tuesday ending a political comeback bid by former 
mayor mike boyle 
with only absentee ballots remaining to be counted morgan had 
56774 votes or 5335 percent to 48115 votes or 4521 percent 
for boyle in the nonpartisan race 
boyle who was recalled from his second term as mayor two years 
ago amid allegations he abused his executive power said during the 
campaign that he was a changed man 
in his concession speech he echoed his campaign theme of omaha 
as a family town and urged supporters to work with morgan to 
solve the citys problems 
we pull together after we fight boyle said 
morgan a real estate manager said in his acceptance speech 
that it was time for the city to move forward and meet the 
challenges of fighting drugs and improving omahas economic base 
im ready to turn the dream of a better omaha into reality 
morgan said 
during the campaign morgan outspent boyle by a margin of nearly 
2to1 
but he said tuesday night that he didnt believe money made the 
difference in the race 
i think this since april 4 the spending has been pretty 
close morgan said we spent more in the primary but its been 
pretty close since then 
boyle said money was a factor 
we were outspent pretty substantially yet i think we were 
doing really well he said before making his concession 
morgan said he believed the endorsements of mayor walt calinger 
and city councilman fred conley played a part in his victory 
we focused on the issues he said the people of the 
community accepted our message our vision of the future 
douglas county election commissioner vickie edwards florine had 
predicted a 60 percent turnout the april 4 primary with seven 
mayoral candidates had record turnout of nearly 100000 registered 
voters in the city of 340000 people 
boyle 45 contended the recall was prompted by his 
controversial management style something he says has changed he 
said during the campaign that hes a recovering alcoholic and 
hasnt had a drink in more than a year 
the effort that led to boyles ouster by a vote of 55275 to 
42832 was led by the group citizens for mature leadership which 
reemerged in an effort to keep him out of office 
morgan 49 is a member of the omaha airport authority was a 
douglas county commissioner in the 1970s and a state senator from 
197172 he said his business experience could benefit the city 
street gangs drugs and economic development in this missouri 
river city were the main campaign issues 
the city has had three mayors since 1985 the city council chose 
council member bernie simon to succeed boyle in 1987 council 
member walt calinger became mayor after simons death in april 
1988 but lost his bid to retain the job in last months primary 
</TEXT>
