the epa said tuesday there are only negligible health risks 
to consumers of food products on which the pesticide is used but 
that the risks are substantially greater to workers who come into 
direct contact with the chemical 
bromoxynil sold under the trade name buctril is used to 
control broadleaf weeds in the growing of field corn wheat 
onions garlic mint and flax 
under the epa directive mixers and other handlers of the 
chemical must wear protective clothing including 
chemicalresistant shoes or boots the manufacturer also must 
provide protective labels warning that exposure to a worker during 
pregnancy could cause birth defects 
