<TEXT>
khmer rouge guerrillas have moved up to 
4000 refugees closer to the heavily shelled cambodian frontier 
evidently to stop relief agencies gaining greater access to them 
relief sources said today 
during the first week of may the communist guerrillas moved 
30004000 refugees from ta luan camp eastward along a route 
bombarded by artillery in april the sources said 
in front of relief officials they loaded the refugees onto 
chinesemade military trucks along with their pigs and entire 
households said sources who spoke on condition of anonymity other 
refugees walked the 2000 people left behind were mostly infirm or 
handicapped 
the guerrillas evidently fear they otherwise will lose control 
over the refugees whom the united nations had planned to move to a 
new camp where they could get medical and other services denied at 
ta luan 
theyre obviously playing games with peoples lives and with 
us one relief official said 
the chinesearmed khmer rouge is the largest guerrilla group 
fighting vietnamese forces that invaded cambodia in 1978 and ousted 
it from power the khmer rouge government had killed hundreds of 
thousands of people in execution chambers and slave labor camps to 
fashion a primitive agrarian society 
relief officials charge that guerrillas in khmer rouge refugee 
camps regularly deny people emergency medical treatment force 
children to carry arms through minefields and execute disobedient 
soldiers 
ta luan is four miles inside thailands eastern trat province 
and is among four khmer rougecontrolled border camps aided by the 
un border relief operation relief officials said the thai 
military crucial backers of the khmer rouge do not seem anxious 
to halt the movements from ta luan 
negotiations with guerrilla leaders have been very 
frustrating sources said they quoted the guerrillas as saying 
people must be moved because they are the soldiers families and 
the families must be with the soldiers 
the guerrillas have been increasingly isolated by the 
international community as talks on ending the war have proceeded 
rapidly in recent months khmer rouge leaders have rejected all 
peace proposals and western officials say they apparently have 
made no attempts to end alleged human rights abuses 
the khmer rouge moved about 7000 people from ta luan to the 
border area in november apparently to populate strategic areas 
inside cambodia gunners inside cambodia responded with heavy 
shelling reportedly inflicting numerous casualties and forcing 
thousands of refugees back to the camp 
relief officials say khmer rouge guerrillas often isolate 
refugees because they want to make sure the refugees are not 
polluted by western influences and do not defect to 
noncommunist resistance groups 
thai officials this week criticized a letter in which 94 us 
congressmen asked that they take steps to end abuses in the camps 
facilitate access by aid officials and allow refugees to move to 
other camps the officials and thai legislsators accused the 
congressmen of interfering in thai affairs and insisted there are 
no human rights violations in the camps 
