periods required of airline flight attendants 
a bill sponsored by rep norman y mineta dcalif would set 
limits on the number of consecutive hours flight attendants must 
work 
as it now stands flight attendants are the only crew members 
not covered by federal aviation administration regulations to limit 
work hours and they have been known to be required to work 24hour 
shifts since the faa requires the flight attendants to be aboard 
for safety reasons the rationale for this oversight is hard to 
figure 
in an emergency passengers depend for their safety on the 
alertness and quick response of cabin attendants a cabin attendant 
who is exhausted from long flights and quick turnarounds with no 
rest break is a potential safety hazard to passengers 
protecting flight attendants from exploitation that hampers 
their performance is public interest legislation that deserves 
speedy enactment 
