<TEXT>
the annual assembly of the world health 
organization today put off for 48 hours a decision on the plos 
controversial bid to be admitted as a state member of the 
166nation un body 
failure by the arab countries to obtain an immediate vote 
boosted hopes of those favoring a compromise to head off a showdown 
with the united states 
washington has threatened to stop all financial support to any 
un agency that grants full membership to the palestine liberation 
organization which now is a nonvoting observer in the united 
nations 
the united states made that threat even though it reveresed a 
longstanding policy earlier this year and opened talks with the plo 
after its chairman yasser arafat recognized israels right to 
exist 
