massif in central switzerland which would run below the 
107yearold 93mile link the tunnel estimated to be completed 
by the year 2005 would match the length of the channel tunnel 
between britain and france planned for 1993 
the old gotthard tunnel handles more than fourfifths of the 
rail freight passing through switzerland but wont be able to cope 
with an increase in traffic expected after the unified european 
economic community market after 1992 
the project also envisions a new 176mile tunnel through mount 
loetschberg connecting the bern region with western switzerland and 
italy that link could be finished by 1997 
parliament is expected to take up the project next winter if 
100000 people sign petitions against the plan it would be put to 
a nationwide vote 
switzerland has about 680 railway tunnels through its mountains 
