<TEXT>
the midgetman intercontinental ballistic 
missile subject of debates on capitol hill and within the bush 
administration will be flight tested for the first time thursday 
the pentagon announced wednesday 
the initial test of the missile designed to be fired from a 
truck launcher will be at vandenberg air force base in california 
the pentagon and air force said in a statement 
the first test will not be made from a mobile launcher but 
rather from a standard concrete launch pad the air force added 
the launch time has been set at 2 pm edt but is subject to 
change the service said 
if all goes according to plan the launch will send the missile 
more than 5000 miles to the pacific test range in the kwajalein 
islands 
the midgetman known formally as the small intercontinental 
ballistic missile is designed to carry a single nuclear warhead to 
a target as far away as 6900 statute miles 
the threestage missile weighs 37000 pounds stands roughly 52 
feet tall and is 46 inches in diameter 
the political controversy involves the issue of whether the 
united states should develop one or two mobile missiles for its 
nuclear arsenal the soviet union already has developed and begun 
deploying two such landmobile missiles while the united 
states has none 
defense secretary dick cheney would prefer to develop only one 
mobile missile a version of the huge 10warhead mx that could be 
carried and launched from a rail car 
president bush recently decided however to pursue development 
of both the mx and midgetman to appease congress 
democratic leaders on capitol hill argue that the nation needs a 
mobile missile to deter the soviet union from attempting a first 
strike against missiles deployed inside silos and that the smaller 
more mobile midgetman is the best alternative 
cheney while accepting the presidents decision has countered 
by saying the pentagon will be hard pressed to afford the 
midgetmans cost roughly 25 billion if 500 are built 
the issue remains controversial despite bushs decision 
because some democrats want to speed up the pace of development for 
the midgetman at the expense of the railmobile mx 
the major contractors on the midgetman include morton thiokol 
inc of brigham city utah which is building the firststage 
rocket motor the aerojet nevada rocket operations of sacramento 
calif which is developing the secondstage motor and the 
aerospace production group of magna utah which is building the 
thirdstage motor 
the martin marietta corp has been hired by the air force to 
oversee assembly and testing and to provide support services the 
truck launcher for the missile is being developed separately by the 
boeing aerospace co in seattle wash 
