spokesman said 
the fernald plant 18 miles northwest of cincinnati processes 
uranium for use in nuclear weapons or as fuel for reactors 
it is the subject of a 300 million suit on behalf of 14000 
people who live or work nearby and believe their health has been 
threatened by radioactive discharges into the air and water the 
government has admitted ignoring or undermining efforts to reduce 
pollution there 
the government has estimated that as much as 552000 pounds of 
radioactive uranium dust may have escaped into the air from the 
plant an engineering consultants report prepared as part of the 
lawsuit said releases could be as high as 31 million pounds over 
37 years 
workers have been complaining that they werent adequately 
protected from or told about the dangerous substances to which they 
were exposed most of those complaints have been directed against 
the plants former operator nlo inc which ran the plant until 
1985 
