involving composite wing construction and phasedarray radars 
but sen alan j dixon dill said a report by the general 
accounting office an investigative arm of congress has already 
concluded that these technologies are well known to us aerospace 
companies 
the evidence clearly before us is that were really not 
getting anything in return dixon said 
