<TEXT>
the sniper who fired an assault rifle into 
downtown boston from a small airplane thwarted five different law 
enforcement agencies with instant communications stateoftheart 
helicopters and sophisticated radar 
murder suspect alfred hunter was captured early wednesday when 
he landed a stolen plane at logan international airport after a 
threehour flight just five minutes before the cessna would have 
run out of fuel 
jet helicopters owned by state police could easily have 
overtaken the cessna if officials had decided to use them said 
trooper david f morrill 
why risk a helicopter chasing an armed person in an 
airplane morrill asked all a helicopter is going to be able 
to do is follow him we did that anyway with the radar if you get 
up there and engage in a shooting match all you do is endanger 
other people 
state police the federal aviation administration the 
massachusetts port authority which operates logan airport 
emergency response crews and three local police departments were 
responded to hunters threehour escapade 
airports all over massachusetts and southern new hampshire were 
alerted 
like the feat of mathias rust the 19yearold west german who 
flew through elaborate soviet border security in a singleengine 
cessna and buzzed red square before landing there hunters buzzing 
the control tower at logan airport and swooping under the tobin 
bridge stunned law enforcement officials 
longtime law enforcment officials said they had never seen 
anything like it 
we could do nothing but wait and try to guess where he was 
going to land said logan airport spokesman phil orlandella we 
could only have made things worse by going up and chasing him 
what if you shoot the guy down and he crashes into a house or 
something said morrill noting that for much of the time hunter 
was flying low over heavily populated areas it just isnt 
feasible you basically have to hope he runs out of fuel 
faa officials tracking hunter from logans control tower twice 
had to scramble out of their perch because the cessna came so close 
they feared it would crash into the tower 
we have a very thick handbook on the rules of air traffic 
control but theres nothing in there about what to do if a maniac 
comes shooting an ak47 at you in the control tower said john 
