<TEXT>
us peanut consumption has jumped 108 
percent since last year proof that good old goobers are becoming 
a posh and fashionable food georgias top peanut official says 
a us department of agriculture report said americans are 
eating 18 percent more peanut butter 72 percent more salted nuts 
and 12 percent more candy bars 
we hope there arent lots of folks out there who arent eating 
peanuts said don koehler executive director of the georgia 
peanut commission but for those who arent eating enough weve 
got a product thats gained a lot of acceptance 
koehler said the usda figures demonstrate the effectiveness of 
the industrys promotional programs the report released on april 
27 compares the first eight months of the peanut marketing year to 
the same period a year earlier 
at that kind of growth rate we could be looking at 85 
million in added sales for producers nationwide koehler said 
to keep pace with increases in consumption and to maintain 
stable prices and supplies the usda increased the national peanut 
quota to 144 million tons this year from 14 million tons last 
year 
koehler is particularly pleased about the 12 percent increase 
in candy consumption 
candy has been kind of flat he said in a recent interview 
it seems we live in a healthconscious society that worries about 
that eating sweets folks are beginning to say wait a minute 
everybody is overkilling food safety food quality and whats 
good to eat once in a while you just like a candy bar 
another reason for the increase in consumption is cost he said 
noting that peanut prices traditionally lag behind the consumer 
price index for food 
you cant buy bologna or hot dogs or any other protein source 
nearly as cheap as you can peanuts he said 
the peanut commission spends more than 1 million annually to 
promote the states top cash crop and cooperates with similar 
groups in florida and alabama in funding the peanut advisory board 
one of the industrys most successful promotional programs has 
been the adultsonly peanut butter club sponsored by the board 
i think we have made it acceptable again for adults to eat 
peanut butter he said its not just kids food any more 
were around 40000 members and they just keep coming in 
this year the commission is focusing on tourists who drive 
through the state the newest official georgia maps at highway 
welcome centers have a picture of a peanut on one side and peanut 
information on the back 
georgia growers who produce nearly half of the nations 
peanuts devoted 688000 acres to the crop last year 
to provide more money for promotion the advisory boards 
headquarters was moved from new york to atlanta where operating 
costs should be about 20 percent less said koehler 
we brought it to the peanut belt he said we felt it was 
a move we needed to make we found we could do an equally effective 
job in atlanta and probably an ever more effective job 
nearly all the peanuts grown in georgia are a type known as 
runners runners account for 801 percent of all the peanuts in 
candy 644 percent of all salted nuts and 757 percent of all 
peanut butter cookies and crackers in addition runners comprise 
865 percent of all peanuts used in peanut butter 
i think people have accepted peanuts as being a good food and 
though theyre reasonably priced we like to think of them as a 
posh invogue food he said we just want people to get out 
there and eat peanuts and know were going to keep growing them 
down here 
