<TEXT>
mexicos inflation rate was 15 percent 
during april the lowest monthly level in nearly 10 years banco de 
mexico said 
the central bank said prices rose 192 percent from april 1988 
through last month 
the announcement tuesday said last months inflation rate was 
the lowest since november 1979 
the government froze wages prices and the peso exchange rate 
feb 29 1988 in a bid to curb inflation that reached a record 
1592 percent in 1987 
consumer prices rose by 517 percent last year under the plan 
although inflation is now under control workers whose wages 
lagged behind price rises have gone on strike recently in the past 
few weeks teachers and bus drivers have walked off the job 
demanding higher pay hikes than the government was willing to offer 
