rule was james ukrop said we never heard it related to 
business but we both saw it 
weve never had to make a decision that wasnt consistent with 
our values he said were very fortunate if we felt we 
couldnt operate our business that way we can sell it i 
personally would opt out 
not selling alcohol goes along with the brothers baptist 
values and they say theyve never considered doing otherwise 
its a nonissue bobby ukrop said the store stays closed 
on sundays he said because if you want to be the best place to 
shop you have to be the best place to work 
we lose some business and gain some business because of 
those policies james ukrop said our friends around the country 
dont think were very bright 
ukrops also gives 10 percent of its pretax profits to charity 
and for the last two years has donated more than 1 million to 
nonprofit groups that get 2 percent of the sales receipts they 
collect 
giving to charity is just the way we think it ought to be 
robert ukrop said 
you cant separate whats family and whats business 
