lowest price for a nearmonth contract since mid1980 
prices for hogs and pork bellies which are sliced to make 
bacon typically rise in may as hog marketings decline due to a 
variety of seasonal factors 
but this years upturn in porkbelly prices is more pronounced 
than usual because the market has been severely depressed for 
nearly a year 
frozen pork bellies averaged about 65 cents a pound from 
mid1981 to mid1988 but prices began falling sharply in the 
spring of 1988 when it became apparent that production was far 
outpacing bacon consumption 
